args:
Chelsea and Mym ask Luca and the prince out
for Valentine's, but their dates are interrupted
by the arrival of imperial forces! As the unlucky
soldiers find themselves overwhelmed by the
loving ladies' wrath, a mysterious figure
watches on from the shadows.
Luuuuccy! I am SO excited for our big\nValentine's date! You are too, right?
Oh, for suâ€”Wait, our what now?
Did I, uh... Did I actually AGREE to a date?
Not out loud! But this was decided from\nthe moment we first met each other.
After all, Valentine's is when you share \nyour love with that special someone!
And there's no one half as special as you!
Yeah, but... Er, I mean, I think I might\nalready be booked that day.
Don't worry, I have your entire calendar\nmemorized! Your next day off is three days\nfrom now, which is the night of our date.
The apple orchard where you usually help\nis closed that day, and you've been bored\nof hunting and fishing for a while now.

And you can't build that new pranking
tool you've been thinking about because
Sarisse will be here and she'd kick your
cute little booty!
Aww, dangit! ...Wait, back up. How do you\nknow all that?!
Anyhoo, I've got the entire date all\nmapped out, so you don't have to worry\nabout a thingie-dingie.
First, we go to a bakery that makes apple\npies just how you like themâ€”plus, they\nhave a special menu just for couples.
Once our hearts and tummies are full,\nwe go shopping for matching earrings\nand look at furniture for our new home.

Oh, and then a pack of baddies will
menace me while I'm getting fitted for
my wedding dress, but you'll swoop in
and rescue me. My hero!

Then we step over their broken, twisted
bodies on the way to the church before
we exchange vows, trade earrings,
and smooch beneath a starry sky!
Oh my gosh, does that not sound like\nthe BEST date EVER?
Yaaay! I've got a date with Luccy! â™ª\nI love you so, so, so, SO much!
(Whoops, I just kinda accepted...\nStill, she has done a lot for me and\neverybody here...)
Oh my! Do you two also have plans\nfor a Valentine's date?
What, are you two going on a date too?
Yeah, we planned it this morning.\n...Apparently.
Hello there, darling! We are going to have\nSO much fun on our Valentine's date,\nwon't we? Won't we? Say yes.
She got me right as I woke up and I was\ntoo groggy to say anything.
Well, can you blame me for not wanting\nsome other hussy to beat me to the punch?
Ooh! Chelsea! Since you're also going out,\nperhaps you can give me a few tips on\nhow these human and sylvan dates work.
To the Valentine's war room to plan, then!\nFarewell, my darling. Taaaaa!
Sorry, Chelsea! Really, REALLY sorry!\nHave you been waiting long?
Oh good, so just a couâ€”YESTERDAY?!
Yup! I wasn't about to be late for a big\nValentine's date with my Luccy!
It took me forever to pick out my clothes,\nand when I noticed the sun coming up\nyesterday, I sorta panicked.
But I KNEW this was the perfect outfit\nto spend Valentine's with my sweetie!

Er, unless you'd prefer different clothes,
in which case, I have multiple stashes
waiting in the area. I want you to be as
happy as you can be, Luccy!
Oh gosh, no. Please don't do that.\nI mean, uh...I like you...just as you...are?
Really?! EEE! Okay then, let's\nget this date started!
Oh wow, MYM?! What a coinkidink!\nYou picked this spot for your date, too?
It was the most intriguing of all the\noptions you suggested, Chelsea.
Is this town especially famous\nor something?
It IS, darling! It's renowned for its roses,\nand has all sorts of delicious Valentine's\nsuperstitions swirling about it!
For example, any couple that spends\nValentine's here is bonded forever!\nTee hee!
Isn't it terribly romantic? And I get to take\nit in with just me, my darling, andâ€”
The glorious army of the Dyrenell Empire\nhereby claims this town!

The rich mana coursing through these
lands demands a more worthy owner.
You rabble have one hour to clear out
before we remove you by the sword!
We ain't gonna let these imperial scum\nget away with this, right?
Not a chance. Everyone! On me, and...\nUm, Mym? ...Chelsea? ...Hello?
I'm going to wreck you fools like the\nhot sun taking down a chocolate heart!

No mercy! No survivors!
No mercy! No survivors!
KILL THEM ALL, MYM!
KILL THEM AAAAALL!
You will pay for the crime of ruining the\nromantic mood here with every speck of\nyour being!
Hang on, Luccy! This won't take more than\na second or twoâ€”just need to delete these\nlosers with the power of love.
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Save the deleting\nfor AFTER we've pushed them away from\nthe town!
